Nearly four years after being incarcerated, a New Jersey man was released from jail this week when murder charges against him were dropped by a state prosecutor. He never had a trial.

Although a 2009 autopsy concluded that the death of Valentino Ianetti's wife was a homicide, new evidence suggests that she took her own life. His wife, Pamela Ianetti, was found dead in the couple's Stanhope home with 47 stab wounds on her body.
